'''Fathimath Fareela''' is a Maldivian film actress.
==Career== The last release of 2010, featured Fareela in [[Yoosuf Shafeeu]]'s drama film ''[[Heyonuvaane]]'' (2010), opposite Shafeeu and [[Sheela Najeeb]].<ref name=Heyonuvaane>{{cite news|url=https://sun.mv/4101 |title="Heyonuvaane" shouldnt be missed |language=Dhivehi |work=Sun |last=Naaif |first=Ahmed |date=27 December 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180929062532/https://archive.mv/dv/articles/wkep |deadurl=yes |archivedate=28 September 2018 |accessdate=28 September 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The story revolves around a male who is victimised of domestic abuse.<ref name=Heyonuvaane/> She played the role of Dr. Rizna Zareer, who meets her lover after six years settled with a marriage.<ref name=HeyonuvaaneReview/> The film received majorly negative reviews from critics though her performance was commended.<ref name=HeyonuvaaneReview>{{cite news|url=https://sun.mv/4544 |title="Heyonuvaane": Year's most boring film|language=Dhivehi |work=Sun |last=Naaif |first=Ahmed |date=17 January 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180929063548/https://archive.mv/dv/articles/dKRr |deadurl=yes |archivedate=26 September 2018 |accessdate=26 September 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Twenty two housefull shows of the film were screened at cinema, declaring it a Mega-Hit and second highest grossing Maldivian release of the year.<ref name=HeyonuvaaneDVD>{{cite news|url=https://sun.mv/12004 |title="Heyonuvaane" DVD releasing on coming Tuesday |language=Dhivehi |work=Sun |last=Raaniya |first=Mariyam |date=24 October 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180929064751/https://archive.mv/dv/articles/2BRk |deadurl=yes |archivedate=28 September 2018 |accessdate=28 September 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>
Fareela began 2011 with Amjad Ibrahim's suspense thriller film ''Hafaraaiy'' alongside Ali Shameel, Mariyam Shakeela, [[Yoosuf Shafeeu]] and Amira Ismail, which was a critical and commercial failure.<ref name=Hafaraaiy/> Based on a real incidence, the film narrates a story of a cannibal woman who is addicted to [[Human cannibalism|eats human flesh]], how she victimised the inhabitants with her face covered in a veil.<ref name=Hafaraaiy/> The film received criticism for its "fragile" plot, "unnecessary" characters though its makeup was appreciated.<ref name=Hafaraaiy/> Ahmed Naif from ''Sun'' wrote: "neither scientifically nor psychologically, its been proven in the film how a chicken addict turns to be a cannibal. The film slides from a suspense thriller to a comedy for its inclusion of inconceivable details". He was displeased with Fareela's role citing it "small and unnecessary". <ref name=Hafaraaiy>{{cite news|url=https://sun.mv/5963 |title=Review of Amjay's Hafaraaiy |language=Dhivehi |work=Sun |last=Naif |first=Ahmed |date=14 March 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181001034052/https://archive.mv/dv/articles/LKMR |deadurl=yes |archivedate=1 October 2018 |accessdate=1 October 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> She next appeared in [[Yoosuf Shafeeu]]'s family drama ''E Bappa'' (2011), featuring an ensemble cast including Hassan Manik, [[Yoosuf Shafeeu]], [[Mohamed Manik]], [[Sheela Najeeb]], Lufshan Shakeeb, Amira Ismail and Mariyam Shakeela.<ref name=EBappa>{{cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nbW6QQCYaSE |title=Reasons why E Bappa Flopped |language=Dhivehi |work=Youtube |author=MNBC |date=4 February 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181003052804/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nbW6QQCYaSE |deadurl=yes |archivedate=3 October 2018 |accessdate=3 October 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> A film about [[fatherhood]] and how he has been treated by his family, received negative reviews for its "typical stereotype style" and was a box office failure.<